(228, 1, '2017-11-26 01:56:34', '2017-11-26 01:56:34', '<h3>Cooking with Honey</h3>\r\n<h5><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><em>Resource: American Beekeeping Federation</em></span></h5>\r\n• Lower baking temperature by 25°. Honey makes baked goods brown faster.\r\n• Measure honey easily by coating cup or spoons with oil or non-stick spray.\r\n• Substitute 2/3 to 3/4 cup of honey per cup of sugar (depending on taste.)\r\n• Decrease the amount of liquids by 1/4 cup per cup of honey used.\r\n... this was changed by adam logan and so this is so dan know that this was changed.', 'Cooking with Honey - Helpful Tips', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cooking-with-honey-helpful-tips', '', '', '2017-11-28 22:13:23', '2017-11-28 22:13:23', '', 0, 'http://beckjohnsonart.com/ciba/?p=228', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(229, 1, '2017-11-26 01:56:34', '2017-11-26 01:56:34', '<h3>Cooking with Honey</h3>\r\n<h5><em>Resource: American Beekeeping Federation</em></h5>\r\n• Lower baking temperature by 25°. Honey makes baked goods brown faster.\r\n• Measure honey easily by coating cup or spoons with oil or non-stick spray.\r\n• Substitute 2/3 to 3/4 cup of honey per cup of sugar (depending on taste.)\r\n• Decrease the amount of liquids by 1/4 cup per cup of honey used.', 'Cooking with Honey - Helpful Tips', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '228-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-11-26 01:56:34', '2017-11-26 01:56:34', '', 228, 'http://beckjohnsonart.com/ciba/2017/11/228-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
